 <ORGANIZATION> Appeals </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Boston </LOCATION> last week ordered <PERSON> Skinner </PERSON> to hold new hearings to determine whether defense lawyers `` knowingly and intentionally'' withheld the report from the families. The original suit contended that four parties were responsible for the pollution: <PERSON> Beatrice </PERSON>; <LOCATION> Riley </LOCATION>; <ORGANIZATION> W.R. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Grace </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>; and <ORGANIZATION> Unifirst </ORGANIZATION>, a uniform supply company. <ORGANIZATION> Unifirst </ORGANIZATION> settled before the trial and <ORGANIZATION> W.R. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Grace </ORGANIZATION> settled for a reported $ 8 million halfway through the trial.
