<HEAD>Trump Indicates He May Seek Control Of Caesars</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTIC CITY, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Developer <PERSON> Donald </PERSON> <PERSON> Trump </PERSON> has notified the federal government that he wants to buy 15 percent or more of <ORGANIZATION> Caesars </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> World </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> stock and that he may seek controlling interest, the hotel and casino company says. In a statement issued late Tuesday, Caesars officials said they were notified that <PERSON> Trump </PERSON> has asked the government for a ruling on whether his investment in Caesars would violate federal antitrust laws. The disclosure sent <PERSON> Caesars </PERSON>' common stock sharply higher today. In midday trading on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Caesars </PERSON> was up $ 4 a share to $ 29.25. But gaming analysts said <PERSON> Trump </PERSON>, who already owns two casinos in <LOCATION> Atlantic </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> and is building a third, would face regulatory obstacles to a move on <LOCATION> Caesars </LOCATION> in both <LOCATION> Nevada </LOCATION>, where Caesars is based, and <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION>, which prohibits single ownership of no more than three casinos. The Los Angeles-based <PERSON> Caesars </PERSON> owns the highly profitable Caesars Hotel Casino here and the <ORGANIZATION> Caesars </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Palace </ORGANIZATION> and <LOCATION> Caesars </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Tahoe </LOCATION> casino hotels in <LOCATION> Nevada </LOCATION>. Neither <PERSON> Trump </PERSON>'s filing nor Caesars' statement indicated how much <ORGANIZATION> Caesars </ORGANIZATION> stock <PERSON> Trump </PERSON> may already own. Tuesday's filing was made under the Hart-Scott-Rodino Act, which requires companies or individuals to seek such a ruling once they have acquired $ 15 million worth of stock in a company. At Tuesday's closing price of $ 25.25 per share, that would translate to about 590,000 shares, or about 2.4 percent of <PERSON> Caesar </PERSON>'s 24.5 million common shares outstanding <PERSON> Susan </PERSON> <PERSON> Heilbron </PERSON>, executive vice president of the <ORGANIZATION> Turmp </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION>, said <PERSON> Trump </PERSON> had no comment on the filing other than to confirm that it was made. She declined to say how much Caesars' stock, if any, <PERSON> Trump </PERSON> already owns According to the Caesars' statement, <PERSON> Trump </PERSON> indicated he `` has the good faith intention, subject to price, availability and necessary approvals, if any,'' to acquire 15 percent of <PERSON> Caesar </PERSON>'s stock. <PERSON> Trump </PERSON>'s filing also said he `` may decide to seek control of -LRB- <ORGANIZATION> Caesars </ORGANIZATION> -RRB- through the acquisition of 50 percent -LRB- or -RRB- more of the outstanding voting securities.'' `` Due to the confusing content of this notice, -LRB- Caesars -RRB- is unable to ascertain Mr. <PERSON> Trump </PERSON>'s plans at this time and has no further comment,'' the company said in its release. One gaming analyst, <PERSON> Marvin </PERSON> <PERSON> Roffman </PERSON> of <ORGANIZATION> Janney </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Montgomery </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Scott </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Philadelphia </LOCATION>, said he doubts that <PERSON> Trump </PERSON> is serious about making a move to acquire <PERSON> Caesars </PERSON>, and said any such move would face serious regulatory opposition in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Nevada </LOCATION>. `` The gaming board in <LOCATION> Nevada </LOCATION> has come out and said it does not particularly relish hostile takeovers, and I can tell you that this would be a hostile takeover because the company will vigorously defend its independence,'' he said. <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <