. So far, he is licensed for two _ Trump Plaza and Trump Castle casino hotels. A third, the massive <PERSON> Taj </PERSON> <PERSON> Mahal </PERSON>, is under construction and expected to be completed in 1990. `` I think he'll sell one anyway in the future, because it does n't make sense to market three in <LOCATION> Atlantic </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>,'' <PERSON> Roffman </PERSON> said `` But the bottom line with this Caesars notice is that <PERSON> Donald </PERSON> <PERSON> Trump </PERSON> is interested in making money, not owning another casino. He simply bought into an undervalued situation and will come out with a profit.'' This is not the first time that <PERSON> Trump </PERSON> has invested in a rival casino company. He made a $ 30 million profit in <ORGANIZATION> Holiday </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> stock and a $ 24 million profit on <ORGANIZATION> Bally </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Manufacturing </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> stock. He also purchased a small amount of stock in the <ORGANIZATION> Golden </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nugget </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, a move that his competitor, <ORGANIZATION> Golden </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nugget </ORGANIZATION> chairman <PERSON> Steve </PERSON> <PERSON> Wynn </PERSON>, called a `` publicity stunt.''
