<HEAD>Macy's Reports $19 Million Loss in First Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> R.H. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Macy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> on Wednesday reported a $ 19 million net loss in its first quarter ended Oct. 29, compared with a net profit of $ 6.4 million a year earlier. The first-quarter loss occurred despite a 20 percent increase in sales, to $ 1.62 billion from $ 1.35 billion. The <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Times </ORGANIZATION>, in Thursday's editions, attributed the loss largely to erratic business and the pressure to stimulate sales by cutting prices. As the retailer sells its goods at an increasingly slim profit _ or even at a loss _ profits have dropped and in some cases vanished, the Times said. <ORGANIZATION> Macy </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION>, which has been privately held for about two years, recently acquired two <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> fashion retailers, <PERSON> Bullock </PERSON>'s and <PERSON> I. </PERSON> <PERSON> Magnin </PERSON>. It is burdened with around $ 5.3 billion in debt from the leveraged buyout by management that took it private and the <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> acquisitions. For its fiscal year ended July 31, <ORGANIZATION> Macy </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> posted a net loss of $ 134 million, of which $ 106 million was incurred in the fourth quarter.
